The paper discusses a new class of convolutional architectures that can learn general invariances and symmetries directly from data. This is a topic that is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed architecture to Capsule Networks, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
